You are implementing a script visual intent parser (`app/api/pipeline/_lib/script-visual-intent.ts`) for a video production pipeline. This module parses markdown script content to determine whether each section requires Remotion-only graphics, Veo cinematic footage, or a hybrid of both.

Requirements

1. Export `ScriptSectionVisualIntent` type: `heading` (string), `normalizedHeading` (string), `veoMarkers` (string[]), `visualLines` (string[]), `bodyLines` (string[]).
2. Export `SectionVisualIntentDecision` type: `mode` ("remotion_only" | "hybrid" | "veo_favored" | "unknown"), `explicitVeo` (boolean), `evidence` (string[]).
3. `normalizeSectionIntentKey(value)` — lowercase, replace `_-` with spaces, split letter/digit boundaries, strip non-alphanumeric, collapse whitespace. Used for fuzzy heading comparison.
4. `parseScriptSectionVisualIntent(content)` — split markdown by `## ` headings into sections. For each section, collect non-empty body lines, lines matching `[visual:` (case-insensitive), and `[veo: ...]` marker text. Filter out sections with empty headings.
5. `findMatchingScriptSectionVisualIntent(sections, target: {id, label})` — build candidate strings from target (label, id, label stripped of `part N:` prefix, id with `part` prefix normalized). Score each section heading against each candidate: exact normalized match=100, condensed (no spaces) match=95, substring inclusion=80, token overlap ratio×70. Return best match if score≥60, else null.
6. `resolveSectionVisualIntent(content, target)` — find matching section, then classify using keyword cue evidence. Decision priority:
   a. Explicit `[veo:]` markers → hybrid, explicitVeo=true
   b. Both cinematic + remotion evidence → hybrid
   c. Any strong cinematic cue OR ≥2 total cinematic cues → hybrid
   d. Only remotion evidence, zero cinematic → remotion_only
   e. Some cinematic evidence (below hybrid threshold) → veo_favored
   f. No evidence → unknown
   Analyze `visualLines` if present, otherwise fall back to `bodyLines`.
7. `resolveSectionHasVeoIntent(content, target)` — boolean wrapper: false if remotion_only, null if unknown or no match, true otherwise.
8. `resolveSectionVeoPromptFromScript(content, target)` — return first non-empty veo marker from matched section, or null.

Cue word lists (case-insensitive substring match against analysis lines):
- STRONG_CINEMATIC_CUES: b-roll, b roll, live action, live-action, cinematic, footage, close-up, close up, wide shot, hard cut, aerial, city street, city skyline
- CINEMATIC_CUES: developer, grandmother, person, people, keyboard, lamplight, hands, office, window, street, rain, rainy, desk, drawer, sock, trash, face, room, night, daylight, walking, typing
- REMOTION_CUES: chart, graph, axis, axes, bar, pie, curve, timeline, infographic, diagram, table, grid, equation, terminal, codebase, diff, matrix, meter, cross section, cross-section, flowchart, labels, annotation
